modules.description: Provides functions to parse, validate, and render self-contained image data structures, operating on byte arrays and custom pixel formats. Includes methods for resizing, cropping, and encoding images in common formats. Used to process and manipulate embedded graphics in real-time applications.

Captures a snapshot of the current program state and saves it to a file with the given name. Operates on internal program metadata and execution context. Used to preserve a checkpoint for debugging or state restoration.
